## Gender Dynamics in the Context of the Wage Gap:

#Shorter Commutes for Women:

Women are more likely to have shorter commutes, potentially reflecting constraints such as caregiving responsibilities or a preference for jobs closer to home.
These constraints might limit their access to higher-paying jobs requiring longer commutes, contributing to the gender wage gap.

#Longer Commutes for Men:

Men dominate the "Long" and "Very Long Commute" categories, suggesting they may have greater flexibility or willingness to travel for work.
This could give men access to better-paying jobs that are geographically distant.


